The sample contains a nationally representative set of young adults aged 18-24, though as previously stated it excludes persons who are currently imprisoned. Persons in this age range had the highest rates of school enrollment as compared to other age spans from 1984 - 1992.5 Observations with missing data on race, ethnicity, family income, and state of residence from the October CPS supplements are excluded, which reduced the sample by approximately 5%.6
